Raul Reza ARANDA, Petitioner, v. Michael B. MUKASEY, Attorney General, Respondent. No. 06-72363. United States Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. *570Submitted March 18, 2008.* Filed March 27, 2008. Raul Reza Aranda, Oxnard, CA, pro se. Stacy S. Paddack, Kurt B. Larson, U.S. Department of Justice, Civil Div./Offiee of Immigration Lit., Washington, DC, District Counsel, Office of the District Counsel, Department of Homeland Security, Los Angeles, CA, Ronald E. Lefevre, Office of the District Counsel, Department of Homeland Security, San Francisco, CA, for Respondent.

Before: CANBY, T.G. NELSON, and BEA, Circuit Judges.

The panel unanimously finds this case suitable for decision without oral argument. See Fed. R.App. P. 34(a)(2).

MEMORANDUM **

Raul Reza Aranda, a native and citizen of Mexico, petitions pro se for review of the Board of Immigration Appeals decision affirming the immigration judge’s denial of petitioner’s application for cancellation of removal.

We lack jurisdiction to consider petitioner’s challenge to the IJ’s extreme hardship determination because it is a nonreviewable discretionary determination. See Romero-Torres v. Ashcroft, 327 F.3d 887, 890 (9th Cir.2003) (citing 8 U.S.C. § 1252(a)(2)(B)).

PETITION FOR REVIEW DISMISSED.

This disposition is not appropriate for publication and is not precedent except as provided by 9 th Cir. R. 36-3.
